# gitleaks per-finding waivers — NARROW, auditable, one line per finding.
# Each entry is <commit>:<file>:<rule>:<line>. A waiver here suppresses ONLY that
# exact finding; the brain-db-password rule stays fully active everywhere else, so a
# genuinely hardcoded secret elsewhere is still caught.
#
# Why these 4 are false positives:
#   The brain-db-password regex captures the first 8+ non-space chars after
#   `PG_PASSWORD =`, which on an env-var READ (`PG_PASSWORD = os.environ.get(...)`)
#   is the CODE `os.environ.get(`, not a secret. The only literal default is the
#   5-char local-dev dockerized password `brain` (postgres:5432/brain, user `brain`)
#   — identical to the Spark suite already on master, never a production credential.
#   These are dev/CI Spark jobs that read the real password from the environment.

